column2: Elite Italian mounted crossbowmen (balestrieri) train here, a multifarious specialization of arms that lends itself especially well to shock and defense tactics, at considerable expense. This military tradition draws from Italian-German (Lombard) origins.
The Basque were renowned for their powerful heavy infantry.

This building prevents barons and vassalized single-province counts from having retinues. If you're seeing it in a count or above's holding, please report it as a bug if it persists for more than a month.
